# 2. イベントに必要なもの

Minori: Oh, what about this place? It looks so new and sparkly! And it's right by the station!
Haruka: It is, but this would put us over the budget too...
Airi: Huh? You two are here pretty early.
Minori: Oh, good morning! Let's make practice a good one!
Airi: You seem awfully excited, Minori.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree. You're just overflowing with enthusiasm.
Minori: That's because I am! I've been coming up with all sorts of ideas for our event!
Airi: Hehe. That's great! Be sure to tell us about them once we have a venue picked out!
Shizuku: By the way, what were you two just talking about?
Haruka: We were looking for some candidate venues. We felt bad about having Hayakawa doing everything for us, and it's a good opportunity to learn more about the venues around here.
Haruka: Unfortunately, we still haven't found a good place for us.
Shizuku: I see. We actually tried looking for some staffing agencies that might be able to help us yesterday too.
Haruka: You did? Did either of you have any luck?
Airi: Well, we have some candidates, but things get pretty expensive around this time of year...
Shizuku: The increase in demand for all the events taking place between Christmas and New Year's in turn also causes prices to increase...
Minori: Money, huh... Even after we talked about what kinds of things we want to do as MORE MORE JUMP!
Shizuku: Yes, but that discussion also came attached with each of being able to “pay our fair share”.
Shizuku: However, putting on an event is a completely different story...
Haruka: Right. Booking a venue and hiring staff alone costs a lot of money...
Minori: Wait, what if I take all the money I've made from working and spend it here...!!
Airi: Oh? “All,” you say?
Minori: W-Well... A little, maybe... Haha...
Haruka: If it's really starting to sound like we won't have enough, I could put in more and...
Airi: No! We already discussed that, didn't we? We each pay our fair share.
Airi: And I'm pretty sure that we've also talked about how it's not a good idea to make some work more than others.
Haruka: Okay. Right... Thanks, Airi.
Airi: With regards to booking a venue and staffing, we'll just have to wait for Nanamin to get back to us.
Haruka: I understand. Hayakawa did mention that she needed to stop by her agency yesterday to discuss another matter...
Haruka: Oh, right on cue...
Haruka: Hello. This is Kiritani speaking.
Nanamin: <Hey, Haruka? Sorry for not getting back to you sooner! Are you free right now?>
Haruka: Yes, we can talk. So... How'd everything go?
Nanamin: <Yeah, about that...>
Haruka: Really? Thank you so much! You've been a huge help!
Minori: ...!
Nanamin: <But...>
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: Right. I guess we don't really have a choice. I'll discuss that with the others...
Haruka: No, we really appreciate it. Again, thank you so much. Okay, talk to you later.
Airi: What'd she say?
Haruka: She said they found a good venue for us.
Minori: What?! Really?!
Haruka: Yes, her agency can apparently book this 500-person hall they use from time to time at a discounted rate.
Haruka: On Christmas Day no less...
Airi: What?! On Christmas Day?!
Shizuku: Every venue's usually booked with some kind of event on Christmas...
Haruka: Based on what Hayakawa just said, her agency originally had it booked for another event, but they ran into some trouble and had to cancel it.
Haruka: This venue was looking for another act to fill that vacancy since they would ultimately be the ones taking the most damage from that happening.
Minori: That's incredible...!
Minori: We really get to put on a Christmas event...?!
Airi: Whoa, hold your horses!
Shizuku: Also, Haruka, you seemed a little concerned towards the end of that conversation.
Haruka: Oh, well... It sounds like Hayakawa can take care of booking a venue for us that's also within our budget...
Haruka: But hiring a staff for our event is going to be a challenge.
Minori: It is?
Haruka: Again, there are events of all shapes and sizes being held this time of year, which causes a shortage in supply in terms of event staff.
Haruka: I'm a little worried about what we should do since Hayakawa's agency won't be able to help us there and how expensive it is to hire through another company...
Airi: These venues usually have their own lighting and sound technicians, but we're gonna need more than that if we're really gonna do a fan meeting...
Shizuku: Yes, we'll need receptionists, people to organize lines, check tickets and such.
Haruka: Exactly. Our fans seem to be expecting quite a bit from us, so we're probably going to need extra hands for other activities besides just the meet and greet...
Minori: Oh, right... There's no event without any event staff...
Minori: Then, let's try looking for people who might be able to fill that role!
Airi: Look for them? How?
Minori: Like, um... Asking our friends to help us!
Shizuku: Oh, that's a wonderful idea! I'll try asking around as well.
Airi: I see... That could actually work. I'll see if anyone in the tea ceremony club can lend us a hand.
Haruka: Our friends... I feel a little bad about asking someone to help us like this on Christmas Day...
Haruka: I'm sure some already have plans, but I suppose there's no harm in asking.
Minori: Yeah! I'll start by asking Kohane!
Minori: Th-They all have plans...!!
Minori: They're all going out with their friends or seeing Christmas events and stuff...
Airi: You too, huh, Minori...?
Minori: Huh? Me too?
Shizuku: I was told the same thing. My friends from club all made plans with their friends or family already.
Haruka: Same. My classmates said they can't come because they're throwing a Christmas party.
Airi: Tis the season so I guess it's to be expected...
Minori: Right...
Haruka: We might not have any other choice but to increase our budget and hire people from a staffing agency...
Airi: Yeah, I'll try looking again to see if there's a company that can help us.
Airi: Oh, hey...!
Shizuku: Hm? What is it, Airi?
Airi: Our MORE MORE JUMP! account got an email from someone...
Minori: Huh? An email?
